
jruby -e "puts 'This is a short program' "
- E option to the interpretor will run the program.

 
jirb
- This is the interactive shell

jruby example_1.rb
- This will run the script in command line. 

jruby -S gem install rspec
- This will install ruby gems made for jruby.

jrubyc example_1.rb
- This will compile our program into a class example.

java -cp .:/usr/share/jruby/lib/jruby.jar example1
- This relies on the class file rendered earlier.
- If you referene some ruby_library.rb you have to compile that extra file manually to ship along side the class. 


